But wait, in Java, for each x in 0 to d, and for each j, check j +x and j -x. Then update dp[i][j]. So for the first part, x ranges from 0 to d, and for the second part, x is from d down to 0, but in Java it's a loop from x=0 to x=d again? Wait no, the code in Java is:

for (int x = 0; x <= d; x++) {
    if (j + x < 1150) dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][j + x] + j);
} Then:

for (int x = d; x >= 0; x--) {
    if (j - x >= 0) {
        dp[i][j] = Math.max(dp[i][j], dp[i - 1][j - x] + j);
    }
} Wait, why two loops?
